{"type":"message","id":"8ffe17f6","parentId":"1e278bfa","timestamp":"2026-03-28T00:01:08.032Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4j0x3fJKqUO6FeawQglAlGql|fc_003269f6235209990169c71a486ea08191a1f3a4bdd20ca8c0","toolName":"sessions_list","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"count\": 23,\n  \"sessions\": [\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:cron:5ca10713-4dc9-4044-aeda-6dd2bc570cb4\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"label\": \"Cron: Atlas OS review - end of day\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Cron: Atlas OS review - end of day\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1774656051349,\n      \"sessionId\": \"415e5419-c4b5-45cb-87e4-ba004ed11242\",\n      \"model\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 53363,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0.367105,\n      \"status\": \"running\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1774656051343,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Gustavo\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\main\\\\sessions\\\\415e5419-c4b5-45cb-87e4-ba004ed11242.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n              \"thinking\": \"**Exploring Notion API use**\\n\\nI need to work with the Notion API, possibly using PowerShell's `invoke-restmethod` with the environment variable for the token. I think I need to query the database and also check out the sessions to find agent sessions. I should inspect the session list actively. It’s crucial to figure out how to contact Prometeo and whether persistent sessions for agents exist. I’ll need to use the sessions_list for that purpose.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Voy a levantar el tablero de Notion y ver qué sesiones/agentes tengo disponibles para coordinar.\",\n              \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0